last_episode_to_air.name: Cat Sh#t Crazy!
last_episode_to_air.overview: Despite the pandemic, Jackson is more determined than ever to help cats in need. He virtually meets a couple's ferocious felines and a family's cat who is eager to escape. Then, he hears from a veterinarian who saved 60 disabled cats and kittens.

episodes.name: He Hates My Boyfriend
episodes.overview: A cat named Bear attacks Hannah's boyfriend; Matt loves his fiance but hates her cat.

episodes.name: Fifi's Ruining My Love Life
episodes.overview: Sean can't deal with his fiance's cat; David's cat Fifi has made his girlfriend feel unwelcome.

episodes.name: Wildcat!
episodes.overview: A couple are surprised to discover that the cat they're fostering is feral; a pair deal with a cat that has extreme mood changes.

episodes.name: Terrorizing My Clients
episodes.overview: A vicious cat named Kleo attacks Tim's cats, keeping him from proposing to his girlfriend, Brooklyn. Heather and Alan's cat Ruby ruins their in-home Pilates studio and threatens their livelihood with her sudden fits of aggression.

episodes.name: Mad Max
episodes.overview: A Bengal cat with jungle energy is disrupting the peace between girlfriends Shanna and Lori. Ned and Kellee's cat, Mad Max, sneaks into their neighbor's apartment, and is too dangerous to be around their soon-to-be-born baby.

episodes.name: On the War Path
episodes.overview: A female cat named Larry with disturbing bouts of aggression threatens to keep Josh and Tara from getting married. War veteran Bobby and his girlfriend In-Hae deal with Marco, a cat that reacts violently towards their tiny dog, Yuki

episodes.name: Pissed Off!
episodes.overview: A vicious cat prevents Rob and Stephanie from adding a baby to their family. Jessica's cat, Mr. Fluff, chases her and her boyfriend Cameron around the house, scratching up everything in sight.

episodes.name: Cat Fight!
episodes.overview: Penny Lane is a crazed cat that hates Laura's roommate, Lizzy, and attacks her at every opportunity. Newlyweds Marty and Karen have just moved into their dream house, but their dream was soon shattered as their cats began to attack each other.

episodes.name: Spitting Mad
episodes.overview: Dorothy and Travis's cat, Polly, vomits out of anger, and attacks the couple. They're afraid their 2-year old son is her next victim. Two sphinx cats, Black Rose and Mathilda, battle for control over Steve and Dierdre's home.

episodes.name: Cat Fight!
episodes.overview: In the Season 3 premiere, a couple's two cats can't be left unsupervised because one of them is too aggressive, while a man and a woman differ on how to deal with their Bengal cat's attacks on its female owner.

episodes.name: My Cat or My Family
episodes.overview: A cat's mood darkens after a couple adopts a kitten; a woman's son is scared of her cat since it has become meaner with age.

episodes.name: Kitty Dearest
episodes.overview: A cat's hissing and scratching confounds its owners, who differ on how to deal with its habits; a woman is ready to give up on a cat because of its unpleasant disposition.

episodes.name: Kitty Jail
episodes.overview: A cat's constant crying wakes its owners up at 4am, and a guest bathroom may be a solution to their situation; a cat that chews on everything has a couple baffled.

episodes.name: Roscoe the Menace
episodes.overview: A couple's cat ruins furniture, knocks things off shelves and climbs window screens in an effort to escape; a cat's frightening behavior could sabotage its owners' wedding plans.

episodes.name: Cat Escape!
episodes.overview: A couple's family won't visit because of a cat's temper; a woman's cat doesn't like her boyfriend.

episodes.name: My Cat Eats Everything!
episodes.overview: A couple's cat eats everything, forcing them to employ childproofing tactics in their home; a woman's cat doesn't take kindly to her male suitors.

episodes.name: My Cat Is a Bully

episodes.name: Big Boi Ruins Our Social Life
episodes.overview: A couple expecting their first child worry how their cat will react to a new member of the family; two women's social lives suffer because of their territorial cat.

episodes.name: Macho Cat
episodes.overview: Cat bully Buddy makes life miserable for fellow feline Lita; a kitty named Princess Puffy Pants urinates on everything.

episodes.name: Graveyard of Peed on Things
episodes.overview: A one-eyed cat with cerebellar hypoplasia torments another feline; a woman's cat urinates on anything and everything.

episodes.name: The White Tornado
episodes.overview: A cat marks everything in its owner's home; a new cat causes trouble for a couple and their older feline.

episodes.name: Chubs
episodes.overview: An aggressive cat worries an expectant couple; a woman who wants to become an animal behaviorist struggles with two fighting felines of her own.

episodes.name: Bea Hates CeCe
episodes.overview: A woman and her sweet cat are terrorized by a nasty feline; a Persian pooh-poohs the use of a litter box.

episodes.name: Cat Horror Show
episodes.overview: A cat-show contestant takes her aggression out on the judges; a man with Crohn's disease cannot stand his cat's constant meowing.

episodes.name: My Cat Ruined My Wedding
episodes.overview: A couple want to move in together, but an uncooperative cat stands in the way of their plans; a demonic feline creates stress for a married couple.

episodes.name: Max Hates My Family
episodes.overview: A hellish feline destroys an Italian family's close-knit bonds; a woman moves in with a friend, not knowing that she owns a psychotic cat.

episodes.name: Buddha Bullies Hector
episodes.overview: Rick's cat, Buddha, bullies his friend and roommate, Hector; a couple is kept sleeping apart by their cat, Dylan.

episodes.name: Evil Kashmir
episodes.overview: A man invites his girlfriend and her foul-tempered feline into his home; two cats that refuse to use a litter box threaten to doom a couple's five-year relationship.

episodes.name: Devil Cat
episodes.overview: A long friendship between three women is put at risk by the evil behavior of one's cat; a bad Bengal cat threatens to get her owner kicked out of her parents' home.

episodes.name: Crazy Daisy
episodes.overview: A shelter cat dubbed "Crazy Daisy" flies into rages and suffers from self-inflicted wounds; she-devil Gizmo's violent ways cause stress for a married couple who want to start a family.

episodes.name: Where Are They Meow?
episodes.overview: Jackson revisits clients from the first four seasons of the show to see how they and their cats are doing, and also checks back on one of his toughest cases.

episodes.name: Sky Diver's Nightmare
episodes.overview: Jackson Galaxy is in Austin, Texas, to help a professional skydiver with two high-flying Savannah cats, Morello and Darwin; a couple's Maine coon cat, Wolfie, is pooping all over the house and covering it up with their stuff.

episodes.name: Blood Thirsty
episodes.overview: Coco is a vicious cat; Foley the cat is dividing newlyweds Joseph and Ruth.

episodes.name: Surprise Attack Cat!
episodes.overview: Little cat Littlez is a big terror; Whisky poops anywhere, everywhere and on whomever.

episodes.name: Stalking Miss Daisy
episodes.overview: Dexter is out to kill Daisy; Sarah's birthday gift, Giver, is not a great gift.

episodes.name: Einstein Hates Izzy
episodes.overview: Einstein the cat ferociously attacks whenever he sees the other house cat, Izzy; a couple expecting their first baby must make a decision about their indoor cat, Ben who was diagnosed with Toxoplasmosis which could threaten the newborn's life.

episodes.name: Puma on the Rampage
episodes.overview: Puma puts married couple's vows to the test; 8-year-old snowshoe cat, Riley is tearing apart 45 year marriage.

episodes.name: 911, My Cat’s Holding Me Hostage!
episodes.overview: Jackson heads to Portland where a family and their cat made national headlines when Lux the cat trapped his family in a room forcing them to call 911.

episodes.name: Mama Mia!
episodes.overview: Greg and Dina have three adorable children and one vicious, hostile cat named Mia; Tenille's cat, Precious is not her namesake.

episodes.name: Multi-Million-Dollar Nightmare
episodes.overview: Frankie the cat pees and poops all over Daniel and Desiree's new mulit-million dollar dream home; newly adopted Dyna hunts has the other cat,Sugar, hiding for her life.

episodes.name: Demon Cat
episodes.overview: Alyssa's cat, Tosh, terrorizes her boyfriend Andy when he moves in; Eric and Kaotar's cat, Vincent, destroys window screens and doors as he continuously tries to escape.

episodes.name: Monty & Tigger
episodes.overview: Monty can't stop himself from eating everything, whilst Thumbelina & Tigger just can't seem to get along.

episodes.name: Reese the Ripper
episodes.overview: Reese has been called the Jack the Ripper of cats; his ferocity has made his owners, George and Beth, prisoners in their own home; Help, Galaxy help!!!

episodes.name: When the Fat Lady Sings
episodes.overview: Barnabas didn't turn out to be the cuddler that Alan and Shannon wanted, but rather a hissing, scratching, biting demon cat whose only kryptonite was opera music.

episodes.name: Appetite for Destruction
episodes.overview: Marco's cat Monty eats anything in sight from shoes to bedspreads, yet Marco blames his new bride Aimee for enabling Monty's bad habit; Leilani and Michael had a happy two-cat household until Leilani brought in two more.

episodes.name: Chloe the Bully
episodes.overview: Jordan's beloved cat Chloe bullies Julie's cat Ketone making these newlywed's new life together a nightmare; Latham and Adrian spent a small fortune renovating their beachfront home in Laguna, but their cat Ducati is destroying their hard work.

episodes.name: Hungry Like the Wolf
episodes.overview: In the season premiere, newlyweds who both have cats bring them together under one roof, but one stalks and bullies its new sibling, which makes it pee all over the house. Meanwhile, a man's cat is so aggressive that his friends won't visit him, and the animal's diet of fried chicken, chips and doughnuts probably don't help its behavior.

episodes.name: Scared to Laugh
episodes.overview: Symone is already an aggressive cat, but the sound of Kelly laughing or crying launches her into a bloodthirsty attack. Alex is getting ready to go off to college, but she's afraid once she leaves her mom, Gena will get rid of her cat Meeko.

episodes.name: Godzilla Attacks!
episodes.overview: Godzilla is deaf and Doug and Talon's other cat Mudgie has a shattered pelvis and can't move her tail. Unable to communicate with each other, Godzilla is attacking Mudgie.

episodes.name: Reese the Ripper
episodes.overview: George and Beth are prisoners in their own home due to their ferocious kitty Reese. Reese is a cat version of Jack the Ripper and Beth is one of his favorite targets.

episodes.name: When the Fat Lady Sings
episodes.overview: Alan and Shannon were looking for a cat they could cuddle, but instead they got Barnabas - a hissing, flesh ripping, demon cat. The only thing that calms Barnabas down is opera music.

episodes.name: Appetite for Destruction
episodes.overview: Marco and Aimee recently got married, but Marco's cat, Monty, is tearing them apart with his appetite for destruction. Marco will eat everything and everything in sight from shoes, to towels, to their bedspread, nothing is safe.

episodes.name: Chloe the Bully
episodes.overview: Jackson visits cat owners and newlyweds Jordan and Julie. What should be a joyous time in their life has turned into a hellish nightmare due to Jordan's beloved cat, Chloe who's bullying Julie's cat Ketone.

episodes.name: Loves Bites!
episodes.overview: Ambreen has been abused by her cat, Calvin for the past 13 years; Josh's girlfriend has not been welcomed into his apartment by his cat, Nico.

episodes.name: Woody the Killer Kitty
episodes.overview: Francesco is terrified daily of his girlfriend's cat, Pootie; happily married Sandy and Phil believe their cat Woody terrorized their deceased cat Velvet.

episodes.name: Paranormal Cat-tivity
episodes.overview: Lola posts a video, out of desperation, seeking a new home for her problematic cat Jimmy Slap; Mike and Patricia have three cats that they adore, the cats just don't adore each other.

episodes.name: My Boyfriend Vs. My Cat
episodes.overview: Reality Star and model Adrianne Curry's Siamese cat Billy Shears is terrorizing her boyfriend, Todd; College student Ashley is held hostage by her bloodthirsty cat Storm.

episodes.name: Darkness Comes Knocking
episodes.overview: Steev and Laura have been dating for seven years, but Steev's cat Darkness is tearing them apart. Mark and Catalina recently moved into their dream home, but their four cats have turned their house into a war zone.

episodes.name: Real Housecat Of Orange County
episodes.overview: Peggy Tanous needs help with her cat Shadow.

episodes.name: Bad Cat Karma
episodes.overview: When Justin gave his cat-obsessed mom a new kitten, Bombadil, he had no idea it would be a gift from hell. Buddhists Tom and Pola were living a harmonious life until they adopted Percy.

episodes.name: Fat Elvis
episodes.overview: A photographer's cat threatens his business by terrorizing his clients and assistant; hostile 21-pound feline Elvis threatens his family.

episodes.name: Psychic Disconnect
episodes.overview: Maryam the pet psychic can communicate with just about any animal...except her vicious cat Lily; Kym discovers a feral colony living behind her home.

episodes.name: Happily Never After
episodes.overview: When Debbie returns home from a trip, she finds her house covered and smelling like cat pee from her boyfriend, Brian's cat Blinkie, who denies the problem. Krisi may have to choose between marriage to her boyfriend Jason and her cat Frankie.

episodes.name: Loves Bites!
episodes.overview: A woman lives in fear of the cat she's had for 13 years because it's constantly biting her; a man's cat relentlessly attacks his girlfriend after she moves in with him.

episodes.name: Woody The Killer Kitty
episodes.overview: A man lives in fear of his girlfriend's cat; a couple worry about their adopted cat's behavior and wonder if it caused their other cat so much anxiety it died.

episodes.name: Paranormal Cat-Tivity
episodes.overview: A woman makes videos of her cat's ferocity in a desperate attempt to find it a new home; a couple's three cats do not get along, and the woman thinks there's a supernatural reason why.

7.name: Season 7
7.overview: From spastic cats that break up relationships to violent felines that put their owners in the hospital, cat behaviorist Jackson Galaxy has seen it all. Follow Jackson as he brings his unique understanding of cats to desperate families on the verge of giving up on their furry companions.

episodes.name: Crazy Cat Opens Doors
episodes.overview: In the Season 8 premiere, a cat's aggressive behavior has a couple worried about their baby, and a cat with a wild side opens doors to get outside and hunt. Also: a "My Cat From Heaven" segment on a lifesaving feline in Ohio.

episodes.name: Katrina Storms In
episodes.overview: A woman feels abused by her cat and is ashamed that she doesn't how to stop it; a family is divided over a cat they rescued from the aftermath of a hurricane because it keeps spraying all over the house.

episodes.name: Four Blind Cats / My Cat From Heaven
episodes.overview: Jackson must rescue Meki and Megan from their cycle of co-dependency before they're both kicked out of Megan's parent's place, or worse; Jackson tutors a bouncer on how to handle his sweet Tasmanian devil of a cat.

episodes.name: Scary Tails
episodes.overview: Skylar the cat is deathly afraid of her own tail; Jackson meets pair of guardians whose cat is destroying the house and attacking people at random.

episodes.name: Breaking Bald
episodes.overview: Two hairless Donskoy cats are out of control in their guardian's home. Also: A woman has spent two decades caring for feral cats in her neighborhood.

episodes.name: Brooklyn Cat Fight
episodes.overview: A woman's afraid of her cat and keeps it in a pet carrier outside her house; a Brooklyn couple are at odds over the feud between their two cats.

episodes.name: Gotham Feral Cats
episodes.overview: Jackson goes to New York City to help a father and son who tend to a feral cat colony in their backyard, but it's getting to be too big of a job. Meanwhile, a couple are concerned about their antisocial cat.

episodes.name: Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Scar
episodes.overview: A cat struggles to adapt to its rescue home, so Jackson takes the unprecedented step of turning to a foster family in the hope that they'll adopt it.

episodes.name: Felines and Frenemies?
episodes.overview: A tour of the Koneko Cat Café in New York City. Also: Two roommates' cats keep attacking each other; a mother and daughter struggle to care for a frightened feral cat.

episodes.name: A Brave New Cat World
episodes.overview: Jackson goes to a shelter in Los Angeles to help an overaggressive cat, and ultimately gets involved in a new concept for the facility.

8.name: Season 8
8.overview: From spastic cats that break up relationships to violent felines that put their owners in the hospital, cat behaviorist Jackson Galaxy has seen it all. Follow Jackson as he brings his unique understanding of cats to desperate families on the verge of giving up on their furry companions.

episodes.name: Scout's Honor
episodes.overview: In the Season 9 premiere, one cat is so afraid of another that torments it that it lives inside a kitchen cabinet; and a cat can use the toilet but otherwise is hyperactive.

episodes.name: Mayday! Mayday!
episodes.overview: A cat guardian about to move to Canada needs help with her two very feral cats. Also: Jackson experiences a vicious, but illuminating, cat attack.

episodes.name: Nightmare on Cat Street
episodes.overview: A troublemaking cat is named after a cinematic serial killer; a couple's cat is lovable but sprays all over the house.

episodes.name: Feral Shop Cat
episodes.overview: Jackson helps a couple whose three cats have been fighting to such extremes they moved into a bigger house just to give their warring felines extra space. The Cat Daddy works with a feral shop cat named Greenie whose spraying is threatening business.

episodes.name: Kitten Impossible: Roadtrip Rescue
episodes.overview: In a first-of-its-kind episode, Jackson takes the show on the road, literally. To save the lives of 50 kittens from LA shelters, the Cat Daddy high-tails 50 orphan kittens in need of a home all the way to his old stomping grounds of Boulder, CO.

episodes.name: Mojito Cat
episodes.overview: Jackson deals with a young man with a genuine cat phobia and then returns to Colorado to keep his favorite kitten from the kitten rescue road trip in her adoptive home. Then he teaches a boy he met at the adoption event how to clicker train a kitten.

episodes.name: Jekyll & Hyde Cat
episodes.overview: Jackson works with a couple who has a blind cat who’s suffering from living in a chaotic environment. He then visits a Jekyll and Hyde cat, Jude, that’s a darling during the day, but a nightmare at night.

episodes.name: A Scratch from the Past
episodes.overview: Jackson works with Tara and her cat Cali, whose traumatic experience with her former cat Mosh, having to be surrendered and euthanized by a local shelter affects her relationship with Cali; Jackson must deal with Kurtis and his cat Kurtis Jr., before Kurtis takes the inhumane option of having his feline namesake declawed.

episodes.name: Bully Cat
episodes.overview: A couple fear having a child because of their aggressive cat, Martini; Jackson tries to keep the peace between a pair of cats that constantly fight, most often in the cat litter.

episodes.name: Bad Max
episodes.overview: Jackson works on the behavior of a hyperactive cat named Mr. Weasley. However, when this Persian cat goes down mid-play, the story takes a completely different turn; Jackson figures out how to move an exiled cat indoors.

episodes.name: Good Kitty Bad Kitty
episodes.overview: Jackson comes to the defense of Good Kitty, a feline who he must help stand up to her two feline attackers. The Cat Daddy also encounters a couple fed up with the way their cats, Tiki and Marley, are eating everything in sight.

episodes.name: Cats in Isolation
episodes.overview: Jackson deals with the drama of a house divided where four cats are constantly at each other's throats. The Cat Daddy also comes to the Living Free Animal Sanctuary's cattery where territorial issues have forced two cats to live in isolation for years.

9.name: Season 9
9.overview: From spastic cats that break up relationships to violent felines that put their owners in the hospital, cat behaviorist Jackson Galaxy has seen it all. Follow Jackson as he brings his unique understanding of cats to desperate families on the verge of giving up on their furry companions.

episodes.name: Posey the Terror
episodes.overview: Jackson faces the highest stakes of the series when he experiences the vicious claws of a troubled cat who's terrorizing a family about to bring home a newborn baby. Jackson meets an inspirational cat named Skinny, as well as Cole and Marmalade.

episodes.name: Ferocious Foster
episodes.overview: Jackson meets an outdoor cat named Henery, who having been forced to live inside, has protested by soaking the place in pee. A desperate foster guardian resorts to Jackson as her only hope to save a cat from being euthanized.

episodes.name: Fluffy's Last Stand
episodes.overview: A mother and daughter are being torn apart by their cat, Missy, who's determined to kill their other cat Fluffy. Jackson meets a tortie named Candy, who's beating up a nine-year-old because she isn't so sweet.

episodes.name: Sister Smackdown
episodes.overview: In Philadelphia, Jackson helps a cat named Charlee rebuild the confidence that her sister cat, Frankie, has nearly beaten out of her. The Cat Daddy must crack the case of a pee-soaked apartment in order help a family with multiple cats.

episodes.name: Philly's Forgotten Cats
episodes.overview: ackson faces one of his greatest challenges when an old friend enlists his help; he is asked to put on a mass trapping event and recruit a new generation of volunteers to save community cats in Philadelphia.

10.overview: From spastic cats that break up relationships to violent felines that put their owners in the hospital, cat behaviorist Jackson Galaxy has seen it all.
